# Project Overview

> A comprehensive guide to the rudder-cli project structure. This rule provides a high-level overview of the codebase organization, main components, and documentation locations to help developers quickly understand the project layout.

This repository contains `rudder-cli`, a command-line tool for interacting with RudderStack services.

## Main Components

- The main entry point is in [cli/cmd/rudder-cli/main.go](mdc:cli/cmd/rudder-cli/main.go)
- Commands are implemented in [cli/internal/cmd](mdc:cli/internal/cmd)
- Core business logic is in [cli/internal/app](mdc:cli/internal/app)

## Project Structure
- `/cli` - Contains all CLI-related code
  - `/cmd` - CLI entry points
  - `/internal` - Internal implementation details
  - `/pkg` - Public packages that can be imported by other projects

